11#ifndef MODULES_AUDIO_PROCESSING_AGC2_ADAPTIVE_DIGITAL_GAIN_APPLIER_H_
12#define MODULES_AUDIO_PROCESSING_AGC2_ADAPTIVE_DIGITAL_GAIN_APPLIER_H_
13
14#include <vector>
15
16#include "modules/audio_processing/agc2/gain_applier.h"
17#include "modules/audio_processing/include/audio_frame_view.h"
18
19namespace webrtc {
20
21class ApmDataDumper;
22
23// TODO(bugs.webrtc.org): Split into `GainAdaptor` and `GainApplier`.
24// Selects the target digital gain, decides when and how quickly to adapt to the
25// target and applies the current gain to 10 ms frames.
26class AdaptiveDigitalGainApplier {
27 public:
28 // Information about a frame to process.
29 struct FrameInfo {
30 float speech_probability; // Probability of speech in the [0, 1] range.
31 float speech_level_dbfs; // Estimated speech level (dBFS).
32 bool speech_level_reliable; // True with reliable speech level estimation.
33 float noise_rms_dbfs; // Estimated noise RMS level (dBFS).
34 float headroom_db; // Headroom (dB).
35 float limiter_envelope_dbfs; // Envelope level from the limiter (dBFS).
36 };
37
38 // Ctor. `adjacent_speech_frames_threshold` indicates how many adjacent speech
39 // frames must be observed in order to consider the sequence as speech.
40 // `max_gain_change_db_per_second` limits the adaptation speed (uniformly
41 // operated across frames). `max_output_noise_level_dbfs` limits the output
42 // noise level. If `dry_run` is true, `Process()` will not modify the audio.
43 AdaptiveDigitalGainApplier(ApmDataDumper* apm_data_dumper,
44 int adjacent_speech_frames_threshold,
45 float max_gain_change_db_per_second,
46 float max_output_noise_level_dbfs,
47 bool dry_run);
48 AdaptiveDigitalGainApplier(const AdaptiveDigitalGainApplier&) = delete;
49 AdaptiveDigitalGainApplier& operator=(const AdaptiveDigitalGainApplier&) =
50 delete;
51
52 void Initialize(int sample_rate_hz, int num_channels);
53
54 // Analyzes `info`, updates the digital gain and applies it to a 10 ms
55 // `frame`. Supports any sample rate supported by APM.
56 void Process(const FrameInfo& info, AudioFrameView<float> frame);
57
58 private:
59 ApmDataDumper* const apm_data_dumper_;
60 GainApplier gain_applier_;
61
62 const int adjacent_speech_frames_threshold_;
63 const float max_gain_change_db_per_10ms_;
64 const float max_output_noise_level_dbfs_;
65 const bool dry_run_;
66
67 int calls_since_last_gain_log_;
68 int frames_to_gain_increase_allowed_;
69 float last_gain_db_;
70
71 std::vector<std::vector<float>> dry_run_frame_;
72 std::vector<float*> dry_run_channels_;
73};
74
75} // namespace webrtc
76
77#endif // MODULES_AUDIO_PROCESSING_AGC2_ADAPTIVE_DIGITAL_GAIN_APPLIER_H_
